  "prompt": "Is Sri Ramakrishna Paramahamsa an avatar?",
  "response": "The question of whether Sri Ramakrishna Paramahamsa was an avatar is a matter of interpretation and belief, with different perspectives among his followers and scholars:\n\n1. Swami Vivekananda, his most prominent disciple, considered Ramakrishna to be an avatar - a divine incarnation who embodied the spiritual essence of multiple religious paths.\n\n2. Many followers of the Ramakrishna Mission believe he was an avatar who demonstrated the universal nature of spiritual truth across different religions.\n\n3. Ramakrishna himself was humble and often referred to himself as a devotee of the Divine Mother Kali.\n\n4. Some view him as a spiritual realized master rather than a traditional avatar in the classical sense.\n\n5. He practiced and realized spiritual truths in multiple religious traditions, including Hinduism, Islam, and Christianity, which some interpret as a sign of his divine nature.\n\nWhile there's no definitive universal consensus, many of his devotees and followers do consider him an avatar or a special spiritual manifestation. However, the ultimate interpretation depends on individual spiritual perspective and belief.\n\nThe most important aspect of his life was his message of religious harmony and spiritual realization, regardless of the avatar classification.",
